description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen in Ysbyty Penrhos Stanley for a permanent Band 7 Ward Sister/Charge Nurse working 37.5 hours per week on a 15 bedded Rehabilitation Ward primarily in the Care of the Elderly Specialty.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Post holder will be required to give leadership and guidance to other team members both registered and unregistered in the assessment planning and implementation of delivering high standards of nursing care.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be part of a busy Community Hospital, and its future development of its role as an important resource in the local community for the population.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron Elaine Hardman&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01407 766000/01407 766062&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;elaine.hardman@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
